SIMPLE: rejoinder
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoinder
<hw>Re*join"der</hw> <pr>(-d?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From F.
<ets>rejoindre</ets>, inf., to join again. See <er>Rejoin</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An answer to a reply; or, in general, an answer or
reply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The defendant's answer to the
plaintiff's replication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Reply; answer; replication. See
<er>Reply</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoinder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoinder
<hw>Re*join"der</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a rejoinder.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoindure</ent>⟦br⟧
